  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intensified fighting between the Congolese Army and rebel groups in North Kivu
had led to an estimated 28,000 internally displaced people. JOAC awarded
Christian Aid GBP 30,000 to provide urgently needed cash for food for 1,500
families (approximately 9,000 people); Tearfund GBP 30,000 towards improved
sanitation and access to clean water; and, Oxfam GBP 30,000 for water,
sanitation and hygiene response.</narrative>
